PR7 training events observation patch
=====================================

This patch is applied by:

  python scripts/third_party/apply_gaussian_splatting_observation_patch.py \
    --third-party-root ./third_party \
    --patch pr7_training_events

The generated patch adds marker-delimited, observation-only hooks to the local
official Gaussian Splatting `train.py` clone.

Markers:

  # VIEWTRUST PR7 OBSERVATION START
  # VIEWTRUST PR7 OBSERVATION END

The patch is intentionally generated by the script instead of committed as a
patched third_party source file. This file documents the patch identity and
server workflow; do not apply it with `patch` directly.

Safety policy:

  - no loss changes
  - no optimizer changes
  - no camera sampling changes
  - no rendering changes
  - no densification threshold or decision changes
  - no pruning or opacity reset decision changes
  - no third_party source is committed to ViewTrust-GS

The observer activates only when:

  VIEWTRUST_ENABLE_TRAINING_EVENTS=1

Otherwise the official trainer should behave as before.

PR7.1 diagnostic behavior:

  - wrapper injects ViewTrust-GS project root into the child trainer PYTHONPATH
  - wrapper preflights observer import before launching training
  - VIEWTRUST_OBSERVER_STRICT=1 re-raises observer failures
  - non-strict observer initialization failures are printed visibly and disable
    event logging

PR7.2 data correctness behavior:

  - visible_gaussian_count uses visibility_filter.detach().bool().sum()
  - visibility_ratio uses visible_gaussian_count / gaussian_count
  - requested_iterations=opt.iterations is passed to the observer summary
  - patch checks require the corrected visibility extraction

PR11.1 scalar timing consistency behavior:

  - iteration_metrics captures gaussian_count immediately after render outputs
    are available
  - render-time radii, visibility, gradients, and gaussian_count are logged
    from the same pre-densification/pre-pruning snapshot
  - post-prune counts remain in densification_events.csv as
    gaussian_count_before / gaussian_count_after / gaussian_count_delta
  - patch checks require viewtrust_gaussian_count_render

PR8 lifecycle note:

  - PR8 is now applied as a separate pr8_gaussian_lifecycle patch
  - apply PR7 first, then apply PR8 when lifecycle logging is needed
